<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{x}+{2}{y}=-{7}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{8}{x}-{7}{y}={38}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({3},-{2}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+{2}{y}=-{7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}=-{7}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{7}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{1}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{\left(\frac{{-{7}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{1}}}}\right)}+-{7}{y}={38}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{8}}{{-{{1}}}}\cdot{\left(-{7}\right)}-\frac{{8}}{{-{{1}}}}{\left({2}\right)}{y}+-{7}{y}={38}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{56}-{\left({16}\right)}{y}+-{7}{y}={38}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{16}{y}+{\left(-{7}\right)}{y}={38}-{56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{16}{y}+{\left(-{7}\right)}{y}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({16}+{\left(-{7}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{y}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{18}}{{9}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{2}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+{2}{\left(-{2}\right)}=-{7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+{\left(-{4}\right)}=-{7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}=-{7}-{\left(-{4}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}=-{3}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{3}}{{-{{1}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={3}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({3},-{2}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

